==French==
===Etymology===
The root 'merde' from French, combined with the French suffix -eux, which is often used to denote that a word is an adjective.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /mɛʁ.dø/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /mER.d2/

===Adjective===
'''merdeux'''
# {{frslang}}: Analogous to the English 'Shitty', covered in shit, turds, excrement.

===Noun===
'''merdeux(-euse)'''
#{{frslang}}: A mischievious or villainous person.

